{"TopicId":147537,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Use RCS and Main engines at the same time?","CreatedByName":"juvilado","CreatedById":106978,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-13T10:23:23Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"juvilado","CreatedById":106978,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-13T10:23:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi, i want to build an HTHL spacecraft for HL in Minmus, and was thinking about using \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003Ercs\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters to compensate vertical descent while still can operate with main engines just in case. Is that possible? How do you do that?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hupf","CreatedById":152424,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-13T10:38:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nYou can very easily operate the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters with the ijklhn keys and the main engines with ctrl/shift in normal flight mode\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters have a tweekable (right-click on them either in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E or even later in flight) that allows them to be activated by the ctrl/shift main engine throttle as well (i.e. boosting the main engine\u0027s thrust)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-13T10:38:33Z\u0022 title=\u002209/13/2016 10:38  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 13, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Hupf\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-13T11:07:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222753628\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147537\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221473763092\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152424\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Hupf\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n29 minutes ago, Hupf said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters have a tweekable (right-click on them either in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E or even later in flight) that allows them to be activated by the ctrl/shift main engine throttle as well (i.e. boosting the main engine\u0027s thrust)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis works well, just be careful to disable the main engine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"katateochi","CreatedById":35181,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-13T12:36:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat I\u0027ve done for some time is to bind the vertical \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E controls (h and n) to the (forward, back) side buttons on my mouse, which lets me keep my left hand on the pitch/roll/throttle controls and my right hand on the mouse\u00A0so I can still control the camera. \u00A0That setup is also very nice for docking.\u003Cbr\u003E\nI\u0027m not sure if KSP lets you bind the forward/back mouse buttons to the controls, I do it using the mouse driver software which lets me bind keyboard function to mouse buttons, so I don\u0027t have to modify KSP binding settings for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E. \u00A0Not possible with all mouse software, but I think most gaming mice drivers can do it.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mycroft","CreatedById":158484,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-13T15:20:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI only use \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E in place of the main engines in docking or if it\u0027s a dire emergency. Otherwise, it\u0027s just not efficient and strong enough. I do not see it as a good idea, especially since \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E is so important for docking, so I would recommend saving it for a last resort, if nothing else will save your crew.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pecan","CreatedById":96332,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-14T15:47:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222753622\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147537\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221473762203\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022106978\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022juvilado\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/13/2016 at 11:23 AM, juvilado said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi, i want to build an HTHL spacecraft for HL in Minmus, and was thinking about using \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003Ercs\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters to compensate vertical descent while still can operate with main engines just in case. Is that possible? How do you do that?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there any specific reason \u003Cem\u003Ewhy\u003C/em\u003E you want to land horizontally on Minmus?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-14T15:47:28Z\u0022 title=\u002209/14/2016 03:47  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 14, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Pecan\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mahnarch","CreatedById":114432,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-14T18:13:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably a buggy he wants to land and then propel with a rocket engine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-14T18:13:33Z\u0022 title=\u002209/14/2016 06:13  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 14, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Mahnarch\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"juvilado","CreatedById":106978,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-14T20:50:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222756165\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147537\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221473868034\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002296332\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Pecan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Pecan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there any specific reason \u003Cem\u003Ewhy\u003C/em\u003E you want to land horizontally on Minmus?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nQuoting Kennedy: \u0022 \u003Ci style=\u0022color:rgb(37,37,37);font-family:sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003Enot\u00A0\u003C/i\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(37,37,37);font-family:sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003Ebecause its\u00A0easy,\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ci style=\u0022color:rgb(37,37,37);font-family:sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003Ebut because its\u00A0hard\u003C/i\u003E \u0022\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:lol:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_laugh.png\u0022 title=\u0022:lol:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222753916\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147537\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221473780034\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022158484\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Mycroft\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 13/9/2016 at 5:20 PM, Mycroft said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI only use \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E in place of the main engines in docking or if it\u0027s a dire emergency. Otherwise, it\u0027s just not efficient and strong enough. I do not see it as a good idea, especially since \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E is so important for docking, so I would recommend saving it for a last resort, if nothing else will save your crew.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E would be for reducing vertical speed while aiming\u00A0to land horizontally. \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E would be on the bottom of the vessel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pecan","CreatedById":96332,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-14T23:06:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222756722\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147537\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221473886215\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022106978\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022juvilado\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, juvilado said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nQuoting Kennedy: \u0022 \u003Ci style=\u0022color:rgb(37,37,37);font-family:sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003Enot\u00A0\u003C/i\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(37,37,37);font-family:sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003Ebecause its\u00A0easy,\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ci style=\u0022color:rgb(37,37,37);font-family:sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003Ebut because its\u00A0hard\u003C/i\u003E \u0022\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:lol:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_laugh.png\u0022 title=\u0022:lol:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E would be for reducing vertical speed while aiming\u00A0to land horizontally. \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E would be on the bottom of the vessel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell yes, except in this case \u0027because it is\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eharder\u003C/em\u003E\u0027, rather than \u00A0\u0027because the only way is hard\u0027. \u00A0No point except itself is needed - have fun :-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mycroft","CreatedById":158484,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-15T06:49:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222756722\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147537\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221473886215\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022106978\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022juvilado\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, juvilado said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nQuoting Kennedy: \u0022 \u003Ci style=\u0022color:rgb(37,37,37);font-family:sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003Enot\u00A0\u003C/i\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(37,37,37);font-family:sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003Ebecause its\u00A0easy,\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ci style=\u0022color:rgb(37,37,37);font-family:sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003Ebut because its\u00A0hard\u003C/i\u003E \u0022\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:lol:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_laugh.png\u0022 title=\u0022:lol:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E would be for reducing vertical speed while aiming\u00A0to land horizontally. \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E would be on the bottom of the vessel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat I did for that was simple: make your craft a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E. Much better!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd actually there are several techniques for landing horizontal craft that aren\u0027t VTOLS on say, the Mun. I\u0027ve done it. But look up Scott Manley, he can show you how to much more clearly...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Corona688","CreatedById":2511,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-15T20:29:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy not slap on some verniers?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"juvilado","CreatedById":106978,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-15T21:41:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222758497\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147537\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221473971360\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00222511\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Corona688\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Corona688 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy not slap on some verniers?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNice idea, ill work on that\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"foamyesque","CreatedById":2982,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-16T21:25:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222756943\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147537\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221473894382\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002296332\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Pecan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2016-09-14 at 5:06 PM, Pecan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell yes, except in this case \u0027because it is\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eharder\u003C/em\u003E\u0027, rather than \u00A0\u0027because the only way is hard\u0027. \u00A0No point except itself is needed - have fun :-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, there\u0027s reasons.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://images.akamai.steamusercontent.com/ugc/268345016162139893/8EF49DF5428FDE3EB503FC87E7EF5484A4A68607/\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u00228EF49DF5428FDE3EB503FC87E7EF5484A4A68607\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://images.akamai.steamusercontent.com/ugc/268345016162554150/77096CFB222AC9E15F7F0C1AF00E77ED27DE4CC4/\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u002277096CFB222AC9E15F7F0C1AF00E77ED27DE4CC4\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWoulda had some trouble parking that on its tail :v\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mycroft","CreatedById":158484,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-16T22:49:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOy! Looks cool! It seems like you landed without incident. I\u0027ll see if I can whip up a few pictures of how to land a spaceplane later on.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}